RediPack rolls are specifically designed to make packing blister packs simple and efficient. MPS RediPack packettes combine the benefits of an MPS packette with in-store manual or automated blister packing. RediPack allows your pharmacy to:
•  Reduce excess space dedicated to blister packing.

MPS RediPack packettes contain all your Customer’s medication in one convenient packette, simplifying your workload and offering your pharmacy a simpler and more efficient way of blister packing. In the RediPack trials the average manual blister packing increased from 8 to 25 packs an hour on average.
The MPS RediPack packettes are packed for easy dispensing by your pharmacist or your automated packing machine into your preferred blister pack consumables.
Order your RediPack rolls via the MPS Medication Management System, HealthStream.
These rolls are specifically packed by dose type, in order to pack in blister columns.
Easy to open RediPack packettes have perforated edges to allow for speedy blister card packing.
RediPack can be used with your preferred blister consumables.
Apply pressure with your roller to securely seal your blister card.
Conduct checks and complete sign offs
– your DAA is ready for your happy Customer.

You can pick up your medication from your pharmacy as often as you need. MPS packs your medication into 14-day rolls.

You can pay for your medication the same way that you pay for your scripts – at your chosen pharmacy – the only difference is that your medication will be packed into packettes for easier dose management.
If there are changes made to your medications, all you need to do is bring your new script to your pharmacist and they can easily adjust the medications dispensed to match your new prescription.
Yes, your pharmacy will dispense your scripts for your medication packette roll order. When your scripts run out, your pharmacist will let you know that you need a new script.
Yes. MPS packs a selection of vitamins that can be included with your medication rolls.

MPS has a range of preferred generic brands that allow us to pass on discounts and keep your costs lower. All generic brands are bioequivalent to their branded counterparts, so you get the same benefits.

In addition to prescription medication, often our Customers also take vitamins, supplements and over-the-counter medications on a daily basis. For a service that saves you time, headaches and hassle, MPS can include your non-prescription pills with your prescription medication.

MPS provides you with MPS Packettes ready for dispensing to your Customers. Our pre-packed Packettes are manufactured in one of our three, TGA-Licensed Dose Manufacturing Facilities. Now you can assist your Customers to take their medication as prescribed – the right dose at the right time. Every time.
•  Small, clear pouches that can hold up to 10 medications for each dose time.
•  Tailor your packettes to your individual requirements.
•  Individually labelled with your medication and dose information, for that dose time.
•  Can be packed at just 5-minute intervals.
•  Manufactured in one of our three, TGA-Licensed Manufacturing Facilities.
•  Your medication can be crushed inside the MPS Packette.
•  The perforated edges allow for easy opening.
•  Small and discreet, they can be slipped into your pocket or handbag ready to go.

As an outsource DAA (Dose Administration Aid) business, MPS offers one solution to manage multiple DAA options. We assist pharmacies and aged care facilities to focus on better health outcomes for their Customers and residents rather than spend time packing DAAs.
Through TGA licensing, MPS facilitates a continuous improvement culture, providing confidence in our quality and offering your pharmacy or aged care facility:

MPS is more than just a packing house and we’ve invested in extensive market research to focus on understanding the Customer. We’ve worked hard to provide an accurate DAA that meets the demands of the market and connects pharmacies and aged care facilities with their Customers.

Market research has indicated that consumers understand the necessity of a DAA, but want their trusted health professionals to discuss their options or reassure them that their choices will bring them a better quality of life. Our focus is on working with pharmacies and aged care facilities to help them identify and discuss options with their Customers and residents.

MPS aims to move forward – it’s about connecting pharmacies and aged care facilities through services and partnerships to assist in providing increased quality of life and care, the ability to stay at home longer and the elimination of preventable medication management incidents.
MPS is looking to the future – a future made possible by connecting Customers and residents to better health outcomes.
